<div id="Idea_3222"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3222-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3222">Replace lights in all government buildings with motion sensor activated lights&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4612-4049">azaleahs</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">5 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">These could be set to turn the lights off if there is no activity in a room or corridor for 30 minutes. If an alarm sounded (maybe a low key bell) just before the lights turned off it would warn people that they should wave or something if they wanted to keep the lights on. A timer on the switch panel would be adjustable up to an hour.</div>
